result.execSummary:
The defendant Joanne Marie Alexander was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Joanne Marie Alexander is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Joanne Marie Alexander was found guilty of Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Penalties for Misdemeanors-Class "B"], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

CO: Lundell, RPR: Val Deiss, Clerk: Webb, ADA: Michael Edward Nieskes, DF ATTY:  Mark J Gherty DF: Joanne Marie Alexander appeared.  Court called at 2:02 p.m.  Set for PTC.  There is an agreement.  DE files a Plea Questionnaire and Waiver of Rights Form with the Court.  Crt reviews plea questionnaire and informs DE of rights.  Crt finds DE freely, voluntarily and knowingly waives rights and makes plea.  Court reads charge and maximum penalty.  DE pleads No Contest to the amended Ct 2 (State Disorderly Conduct).  No Contest Plea is entered.  Court reviews the North Hudson Police Department report.  Crt accepts plea, finds factual basis and finds the DE adjudicated guilty of the amended Ct 2 (State Disorderly Conduct). On motion of the State, Crt dismisses Ct 1. Sentencing arguments. Crt orders:

Court orders $200 for DNA Surcharge and $50.00 for Court Costs and Court suspends the rest of the fine.
- Apply money on file and refund remaining balance to payor
- DE to go down to the jail and submit to a DNA test
- 20 days to appeal

Bond on file.

  It is hereby ordered, as a condition of the defendant's bond/bail in the above-captioned case, that he/she have absolutely NO CONTACT whatsoever with the complaining witness, or with any of the following named persons and/or locations, Mallalieu Inn.  The term "no contact" is hereby defined as no contact in person, by telephone, by way of electronic device, email, facsimile, social media including but not limited to texting, Facebook, Twitter, contact through the mail, and/or through a third person.  The aforementioned condition of bond/bail is set pursuant to Sec. 969.02(3)(d), Wis Stats.

Further, it is ORDERED that if the defendant fails to comply with the conditions of his/her bond/bail that he/she may be charged with the offense of bailjumping contrary to Sec. 946.49(1)(a), Wis. Stats.
